reviews_data.review_text: They offer various pastries. The pistachio cheesecake is light but delicious. My husband loves the eclair. But we all agree that the fillings in both of our croissants are too sweet for our taste buds. And their croissants are more dense than French flakey style. We would love to come back to try out more pastries in the future.

Best Sfogliatella I've had in the carolinas
Almond cookie was amazing too.
Cappuccino was good, its Italian style beans, stronger if you know what I mean.
Nice bakery, small space, good location.
Hands down my favorite cafe and dessert spot in the south end. Atmosphere and staff make it a blast to be there, and the coffee and desserts are A+
i can’t stop thinking about the lobster tail 🤤

I came, I saw, I got laughed at. I know what you might be thinking - wow that’s an intense start to a review… but it was true nonetheless. I came with my 8yo daughter and realized it’s replaced pepper box. I thought that was a good sign. There weren’t a lot of options (tarts, lobster tails, cookies) so I was looking for a happy medium for us while my daughter’s eyes were bigger than her head. Meanwhile a guy behind the counter eyed me and spoke in Spanish which I don’t think he realized I knew. It was a simple question because I gave a dessert the wrong name. His female coworker answered and they waited for us as we kept looking. Then as I spoke to my daughter they broke out in laughter without saying a word. The kind of laughter middle school girls break into when they’re being …middle school girls.

So we left. When you go just make sure you’re not looking for service.
Enjoyed what we got.

Got the blue butterfly matcha. There is no matcha. They’re calling powdered blue butterfly pea matcha, which is in fact just a marketing gimmick. It’s not real matcha. I basically paid $6 for blue milk. Tried telling cashier and owner and they dismissed me and said I don’t know what I’m talking about.

Edit to add: crazy that they are doubling down again in the response that it is matcha. It contains no green tea and should never be called matcha. Maybe do your research properly before trying to sail on the matcha trend for profit. A quick google search will tell you. I did order this drink before and whoever made it previously did add both matcha and blue butterfly pea. That is why I wanted to order it again but they insist that it was never served that way. Which is fine, maybe whoever served me that day just knew the difference and actually made a blue butterfly pea matcha latte properly. Not a blue butterfly pea latte. Do your research and rename the item on the menu if you are about honest and care because doubling down that it is matcha is the opposite. I also want to add that they can speak Spanish and was talking about me right in front of me too.

Edit to add again because if they are about honest and care then don’t put the biscotti sign in front of the cookies 🤣
reviews_data.owner_answer:
We’re sorry you were disappointed with the Blue Butterfly Matcha. It’s made with butterfly pea powder, not traditional green matcha, and we understand that may have been confusing. However butterfly pea powder is called Blue Matcha and below is the link to the product: 
https://a.co/d/cZuwbCl
We did offer to make you a green matcha instead, but you declined and insisted you’d previously had a blue and green matcha mix here, which we’ve never served.
We work hard to build our brand with honesty and care, and it feels unfair to receive a review like this after offering a solution. If you’d like to chat further, feel free to reach out directly.

reviews_data.review_text: Finally a new bakery in town! Must try! I got pistachio everything! 🙌🏻🙌🏻🙌🏻🙌🏻🙌🏻

Had to check out the newest addition to South End. You’ll find a large selection of pastries, which I hope to come back and try more of! I had the Dolce & Amaro latte, which has tiramisu and mocha. It’s on the sweeter side of lattes. I’ll have to try a more authentic Italian coffee like a macchiato next time. The pistachio croissant had a delicious filling. It’s not as flaky and buttery as a French croissant, a bit more dense. Overall, it was enjoyable and I look forward to trying some of the other sweet treats!

The staff here are always so amazing and kind!! The atmosphere is calming and has a tucked away, cozy feeling. Plus the pastries are delicious and the coffee is great too! Definitely recommend the tiramisu latte!
Stopped into this new spot in Southend and really enjoyed my tiramisu latte and lobster tail. Reasonably priced coffee and service was great. I will be back.
Cute addition to south end! Really enjoyed their iced lattes and tiramisu. Loved the indoor and outdoor space.
This place made me want to have a cigarette. I don’t smoke. 5 stars
Great new spot, fresh pastries & perfect vibe to hang out in the shade
Delicious coffee! We tried the gluten free eclair and it was so good.
Fantastic experience!
Talk about a slice of Italy in South End! You have to try this Italian Bakery it's authentic, delicious, and some of the best I've had down south!
The best!
Cannolis were excellent. Their other pastries looked great as well. I plan on coming back
Damn! Place has amazing sweets and coffee.
The pistachio hazelnut cake tastes INCREDIBLE and looks absolutelygorgeous. I also grabbed a croissant with Chantilly cream and fresh strawberries (literally perfect).

Highly recommended !!
The pastry is so good !
Love the place and the service is amazing and excellent 🎉
The tres leches was just fantastic, so delicious. Cortado and iced coffee were incredible too. New favorite bakery in Charlotte.
Perfect,  just like the Greensboro location.
amazing and delicious!
New open store with authentic Italian bakery and super reasonable price. Definitely 5 stars.
🤤 Absolutely love this bakery! Pastries are to die for, the pistachio filling is amazing! Very authentic and high quality. A must visit in Charlotte. A great way to please a crowd or treat yourself 💕

“This bakery is a gem in the city. The staff is extremely friendly. The pastries are delicious and of the highest quality, truly something unique that wasn’t available here before. Plus, the location is perfect, in a lovely area.”
The pastries are fresh and delicious. This is definitely my new favorite bakery.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you Araminta. Will see you soon.

reviews_data.review_text:
This place is nothing but absolutely
amazing.
Absolute best bakery in Charlotte!
Highly recommend! From the quality & taste of the food & drinks to the great service& ambience, everything is amazing! Don’t miss out on checking out this spot!!
Highly recommended.
Just incredible. So delicious.

Amazing pastries, desserts and coffee. I’ve taken a variety of pastries and cake slices to parties and everybody was amazed. The ingredients are all imported from Italy and you can feel it in the quality of their food.

If you’re looking for an authentic taste of Italy, look no further! From the moment you step inside, you’re greeted with the warm, comforting aroma of freshly baked bread, pastries, and espresso. Every item I’ve tried—from the perfectly crisp cannoli to the pillowy focaccia—is made to perfection. Their lobster roll pistachio croissant is hands-down one of the best I’ve ever had—light, creamy, and perfectly balanced. The staff is friendly, knowledgeable, and always ready to offer great recommendations. Kiara and Jen took great care of us. A must-visit for anyone who loves Italian baked goods—this place is a gem!
Los mejores postres y cafés  🍰 ☕️
To say this is the best cup of coffee in the neighborhood is an understatement! Good quality coffee for a good price, and the service is excellent — reminds me of my fave coffee shop in my hometown.
I have been to their Greensboro location and I am delighted they opened a Charlotte  location. They can custom make your cake. Pistachio cake it’s out of this world

This bakery is a true gem! Their croissants are flaky and buttery and their pastries are moist and delicious. Great selection of coffees. I have tried their location in Greensboro and they don’t disappoint! Friendly staff too!
My favorite bakery - now in Charlotte!! Real italian tastes - go for the zeppole.
Charlotte's best desserts! 😋

A Sweet Slice of Heaven – Dolce & Amaro Delivers Perfection

If there’s one place in town that feels like a warm hug wrapped in the scent of fresh-baked pastries, it’s Dolce & Amaro. From the moment you walk through the door, you’re greeted by the rich aroma of buttery croissants, delicate vanilla, and just a hint of espresso – a sensory preview of the magic to come.

Every item behind the glass is a work of art. The pastries are not only visually stunning but consistently fresh, flaky, and melt-in-your-mouth delicious. Their almond croissants are hands down the best I’ve had – crisp on the outside, tender within, with a generous almond filling that somehow feels indulgent and balanced all at once.

Their cakes are where this place truly shines. Whether it’s a classic tiramisu, a pistachio mousse dome, or one of their rotating seasonal specials, each dessert showcases incredible attention to detail, balanced sweetness, and rich, layered flavors. It’s clear the bakers here don’t just follow recipes – they tell stories through sugar and flour.

The staff is kind, patient, and clearly passionate about what they do. They’ll happily explain ingredients, make recommendations, or even help you pair the perfect pastry with a coffee or tea.

Dolce & Amaro isn’t just a bakery – it’s an experience, one that elevates the everyday treat into something memorable. Whether you’re grabbing a morning croissant or picking up an elegant dessert for a special occasion, this little gem never disappoints. Five stars, without a doubt.

Came across of this new Italian bakery in South End. Everything tastes super fresh and homemade—the kind of stuff that makes your day better. I got a cappuccino and a lobster tail and were exactly like the ones I had in Italy. You can tell they put real care into everything. This will be my favorite spot to grab a treat and seriously good coffee.
This is hands down the best bakery in CLT, prices not only are reasonable but for the quality they seem like a steal. HIGHLY RECOMMEND!!! 5 STAR
